WEBVTT

00:07.137 --> 00:13.013
♪

00:24.720 --> 00:28.637
[seagulls squawking]

01:17.338 --> 01:18.730
[dog barks]

01:22.343 --> 01:23.648
[barking continues]

01:34.572 --> 01:35.530
[dog panting]

01:35.660 --> 01:37.097
Come on, Emily.

01:41.797 --> 01:43.103
[coughs]

01:57.856 --> 01:59.119
- [dog whines]
- [beep]

02:02.426 --> 02:04.820
I know, Emily, I know.

02:04.950 --> 02:07.127
It's just impossible
to sleep here.

02:48.864 --> 02:51.171
[engine revving]

02:51.301 --> 02:54.043
Look, Jack, I know you love her.

02:54.174 --> 02:56.393
I don't wanna fucking hear
about it, Grant, all right?

03:04.836 --> 03:06.534
[line ringing]

03:06.664 --> 03:09.276
[phone ringing]

03:09.406 --> 03:10.886
MAN: Where's my money, Jack?

03:11.016 --> 03:12.627
I wanna see my wife first.

03:12.757 --> 03:13.802
[hangs up]

03:13.932 --> 03:14.890
Fuck.

03:15.020 --> 03:16.370
Don't play games with him.

03:16.500 --> 03:18.850
Just get it done and get out.

03:18.981 --> 03:20.156
[line ringing]

03:23.551 --> 03:25.205
Let's see the money first.

03:25.335 --> 03:26.684
[beep]

03:46.661 --> 03:47.749
[gun cocks]

04:01.719 --> 04:04.244
She starts walking,
then your man picks up the bag.

04:14.341 --> 04:15.472
All right, pick it up.

04:20.738 --> 04:22.044
Ronny, move.

04:27.745 --> 04:29.051
JACK: Ronny.

04:29.181 --> 04:31.358
GRANT: Something not right here.

04:33.664 --> 04:35.753
JACK: Ronny, move!

04:43.848 --> 04:46.721
JACK: Passed 1,000 days now.

04:46.851 --> 04:50.377
The memories of that night,
still fragments.

04:50.507 --> 04:52.770
Can't make much sense
of any of it.

04:55.425 --> 04:58.080
Veronique, Ronny.

05:03.041 --> 05:04.521
It's still so real.

05:04.652 --> 05:08.046
It's as if she possesses me.

05:08.177 --> 05:09.613
But Ronny is dead.

05:12.268 --> 05:14.879
There's no more now
than a constant echo.

05:16.272 --> 05:18.056
Like an imaginary companion.

05:24.498 --> 05:25.455
Come.

05:32.244 --> 05:33.637
Come on, Emily.

05:37.641 --> 05:39.426
Time stands still,

05:39.556 --> 05:42.080
and I find myself counting  the days stuck on this island.

05:56.834 --> 06:00.098
I've improvised
some kind of life out here,

06:00.229 --> 06:02.405
but she still haunts me.

06:04.886 --> 06:07.323
Could I have done more
to prevent her death?

06:07.454 --> 06:12.067
Can't move on till I can
put the pieces back together.

06:13.634 --> 06:15.331
[barking]

06:32.000 --> 06:32.914
[beep]

06:35.046 --> 06:38.180
WOMAN: Pawn to bishop four.
How's the weather?

06:38.310 --> 06:41.749
JACK: Fleet, my lawyer
in London

06:41.879 --> 06:44.099
and one remaining contact
with the outside world.

06:44.229 --> 06:47.450
She's desperate to know where
I am, but can I trust her?

06:47.581 --> 06:49.800
Can I trust anyone?

06:49.931 --> 06:52.194
It's warmer in Aus.

06:52.324 --> 06:54.109
JACK: Knight to bishop three.

06:54.239 --> 06:56.285
FLEET: It's not
your money, Jack.

07:13.998 --> 07:15.783
VERONIQUE:
Come back to me, Jack.

07:15.913 --> 07:20.091
Wherever we run,
he will always come for us.

07:20.222 --> 07:23.312
TV ANNOUNCER: He's gonna
be shadowed by Kosanovi.

07:23.443 --> 07:25.227
The two number eights
may be seeing

07:25.357 --> 07:27.098
quite a lot of each other.

07:27.229 --> 07:29.274
They had a real battle
in the league match

07:29.405 --> 07:31.451
earlier this season.

07:31.581 --> 07:35.803
Petroskov for Drayton,

07:35.933 --> 07:38.109
Murdoch's on the move,
and he's found him.

07:38.240 --> 07:41.286
This is Buck,
laid off for Harry Page.

07:41.417 --> 07:44.289
Crosses Goode, Murdoch sweeps. Stracken!

07:44.420 --> 07:45.900
Oh, yes!

07:46.030 --> 07:48.163
Jack Stracken scores!

07:48.293 --> 07:50.513
It was a career
cut cruelly short by injury.

07:50.644 --> 07:52.776
Jack Stracken was
never able to realize

07:52.907 --> 07:54.474
his full potential
as a player.

07:54.604 --> 07:56.693
His Cup final winner
for Drayton United,

07:56.824 --> 07:59.087
never forgotten,
but only a memory now.

07:59.217 --> 08:01.611
[phone buzzing]

08:02.743 --> 08:04.179
[sighs]

08:21.196 --> 08:23.590
Up, up, come here, come here.

08:28.420 --> 08:30.292
Hey, get off now.

08:33.208 --> 08:34.514
[ringing]

08:35.645 --> 08:36.777
Hello?

08:36.907 --> 08:38.605
It's me.

08:38.735 --> 08:41.564
It's 5:30
on a Sunday morning, Jack.

08:41.695 --> 08:42.826
I know.

08:44.480 --> 08:46.613
What time is it with you?

08:47.875 --> 08:49.529
What's the latest?

08:49.659 --> 08:52.619
Gosh, Jack, you've been away
three years now.

08:52.749 --> 08:54.621
They bought a new striker,

08:54.751 --> 08:56.753
got a few issues
with the stadium.

08:56.884 --> 08:58.625
They are still assigning Karim,

08:58.755 --> 09:00.757
but he's gotta surface
at some point.

09:00.888 --> 09:04.761
Look, there's nothing new
to report. Just lie low.

09:04.892 --> 09:06.676
I take it the money
is still safe.

09:09.113 --> 09:11.855
- Yeah.
- I can post a man with you.

09:11.986 --> 09:14.031
No, no, I'm fine.

09:14.162 --> 09:18.296
- But it's still all a blur?
- Yeah, I, um...

09:18.427 --> 09:20.081
I remember that smell.

09:20.211 --> 09:22.518
Yeah, well,
smell's the most vivid thing.

09:22.649 --> 09:25.042
Look, you know,
what he did to her,

09:25.173 --> 09:27.218
nothing you could have done
would have made any difference,

09:27.349 --> 09:28.785
money or no money.

09:28.916 --> 09:30.308
So you keep telling me,

09:30.439 --> 09:32.963
I just need to put the pieces
back together.

09:33.094 --> 09:36.358
I can't help you
if you don't trust me.

09:36.488 --> 09:39.187
For God's sake, Jack, you'd be
dead if I hadn't got you out.

09:39.317 --> 09:40.884
You're the only one
I can trust.

09:41.015 --> 09:43.974
So then tell me where you are
and let me help you.

09:46.150 --> 09:48.022
I'm not ready for that yet.

09:50.851 --> 09:52.722
It's not your money, Jack.

09:54.419 --> 09:56.421
JACK: We'd been happy once.

09:56.552 --> 09:58.685
Seems like a lifetime ago.

09:58.815 --> 10:00.687
Almost there.

10:04.212 --> 10:06.606
- Just a couple more.
- It's cold.

10:06.736 --> 10:09.434
[camera clicking]

10:09.565 --> 10:11.741
[speaking French]

10:16.616 --> 10:18.835
Just because I'm French.

10:21.664 --> 10:23.666
That's sweet.
[giggles]

10:23.797 --> 10:24.798
Do you miss it?

10:24.928 --> 10:26.364
Football?

10:26.495 --> 10:27.757
Yes.

10:27.888 --> 10:29.716
I miss scoring.

10:30.847 --> 10:32.414
It's a great feeling.

10:32.544 --> 10:34.155
Better than sex?

10:34.285 --> 10:36.940
No comment.
[chuckles]

10:38.855 --> 10:40.988
But there are other ways
to play the game.

10:41.118 --> 10:42.250
Like what?

10:42.380 --> 10:45.383
Manager, CEO, chairman.

10:45.514 --> 10:47.647
Are you serious?

10:49.300 --> 10:52.129
You're talking about
owning the club.

10:52.260 --> 10:55.655
Is that possible?

10:55.785 --> 10:57.569
Anything's possible.

11:01.748 --> 11:04.402
What about us?

11:04.533 --> 11:07.318
This is all about us, Ronny.

11:07.449 --> 11:10.234
We can roll the dice,
buy a big stake in the club,

11:10.365 --> 11:12.976
climb as high as we can
for a few years,

11:13.107 --> 11:18.155
then we sell out, buy a little
winery in Australia.

11:18.286 --> 11:19.896
Nah.

11:21.550 --> 11:25.597
Penthouses, luxury yachts,
champagne.

11:25.728 --> 11:28.165
Who wouldn't want
a life like that?

11:29.906 --> 11:31.734
Jack Stracken.

12:30.488 --> 12:31.968
[whines]

12:36.538 --> 12:37.931
Are you sure, Mr. Leyton?

12:38.061 --> 12:40.847
Oh, yeah.
In a tall glass.

12:40.977 --> 12:43.197
- What's your story?
- One more, please.

12:43.327 --> 12:45.590
Another one, please.

12:45.721 --> 12:47.679
I'll have another one.

12:47.810 --> 12:49.203
And I'll have another one.

12:49.333 --> 12:50.378
WOMAN: Where are you from,
Angela?

12:50.508 --> 12:51.945
ANGELA: I'm from Dublin.

12:58.342 --> 12:59.735
MAN: Angela.
ANGELA: Hey, senor.

12:59.866 --> 13:02.651
Good news.
So you're hired. Welcome.

13:02.782 --> 13:04.305
- Great.
- Can you start tonight?

13:04.435 --> 13:06.916
- Sure.
- All right, good.

13:11.268 --> 13:12.617
Come on, Emily.

13:17.013 --> 13:19.276
Oh, isn't he gorgeous?

13:19.407 --> 13:20.669
- She.
- Aww.

13:20.800 --> 13:22.366
What's her name?

13:22.497 --> 13:24.586
VERONIQUE:
Drink to remember, Jack.

13:37.860 --> 13:40.297
Are you having fun,
Mr. Leyton?

13:40.428 --> 13:42.212
Yeah, yes, Steinjo, whatever.

13:42.343 --> 13:43.648
Okay.

13:52.570 --> 13:53.484
[tires screeching]

13:53.615 --> 13:55.095
[screams]

13:57.488 --> 13:59.099
TV ANNOUNCER:
Realized his potential,

13:59.229 --> 14:01.405
his Cup final winner
for Drayton United,

14:01.536 --> 14:03.581
only a memory now.

14:03.712 --> 14:05.714
VERONIQUE:
Come back to me, Jack.

14:13.026 --> 14:14.418
Emily.

14:17.944 --> 14:19.728
Emily?

14:44.100 --> 14:45.319
Emily.

14:48.017 --> 14:50.802
[seagull squawking]

14:54.371 --> 14:55.720
Emily!

14:57.287 --> 15:00.290
[distant thumping]

15:06.688 --> 15:10.039
[thumping continues]

15:17.394 --> 15:20.180
[thumping]

15:24.532 --> 15:26.403
For Christ's sake, Emily.

15:29.232 --> 15:30.407
Come here.

15:30.538 --> 15:32.453
[whining]

15:35.151 --> 15:36.065
Come.

15:39.547 --> 15:42.115
VERONIQUE:
Drink to remember, Jack.

15:47.163 --> 15:49.861
JACK: I need a change
of atmosphere.

15:49.992 --> 15:53.300
Can't get back those ten years.

15:53.430 --> 15:55.955
I have a vision.

15:56.085 --> 15:58.435
A bar on a lake,

15:58.566 --> 16:00.960
drawing me to it
like a magnet.

16:02.831 --> 16:04.789
I feel like I know this place.

16:28.509 --> 16:30.380
The usual, Mr. Leyton?

16:30.511 --> 16:33.644
- And one for yourself, Tom.
- Thank you very much.

16:34.906 --> 16:36.343
What's all this?

16:36.473 --> 16:39.215
TOM: Zaney's big new draw
for the punters.

16:39.346 --> 16:42.001
- Music and footie.
- You fancy a game?

16:42.131 --> 16:44.264
I would, but Zaney
don't like me playing.

16:44.394 --> 16:45.352
Fair enough.

16:53.969 --> 16:55.144
MAN: Hey.

16:56.276 --> 16:57.929
Yeah, yeah.

17:00.019 --> 17:02.064
- It's a hundred quid.
- You said fifty.

17:02.195 --> 17:04.849
It's a hundred quid.
Take it or leave it.

17:04.980 --> 17:07.026
Is she cool with that?

17:11.769 --> 17:12.727
Hey, Tom.

17:12.857 --> 17:13.989
How's it going, Zaney?

17:14.120 --> 17:16.470
- Good, good. And you?
- Not bad.

17:24.217 --> 17:25.957
What was going on out there?

17:26.088 --> 17:28.960
Just business, Mr. Leyton.
I'm sure you understand.

17:30.745 --> 17:33.356
Fancy a hiding?

17:41.190 --> 17:43.236
All right, ready?

17:47.805 --> 17:49.981
Dropping by
for the show tonight?

17:50.112 --> 17:51.157
Show? What show?

17:51.287 --> 17:53.159
Show. You know the show.

17:53.289 --> 17:54.377
Oh, yeah, yeah, the show.

17:54.508 --> 17:55.857
Come on, come on!

17:58.816 --> 18:00.905
- Zaney.
- Yeah.

18:01.036 --> 18:02.994
I meant to ask. Where'd you get
that name of yours?

18:03.125 --> 18:06.563
School. Girls reckoned
I looked like

18:06.694 --> 18:08.783
that actor in Titanic,
Billy Zane.

18:08.913 --> 18:10.785
- Can't see it.
- Guess it stuck.

18:10.915 --> 18:14.267
Yes! One-nil.
Going for the kill.

18:20.316 --> 18:21.709
Excuse us a minute.

18:23.450 --> 18:25.365
Hey.

18:25.495 --> 18:27.062
Hey. Sorry I'm late.

18:27.193 --> 18:28.498
I was just
looking for something.

18:28.629 --> 18:30.761
- Yeah, yeah.
- Yeah.

18:35.288 --> 18:37.594
- Who's the girl?
- She's here for the holidays.

18:37.725 --> 18:40.380
You know, extra cash,
bar work.

18:40.510 --> 18:42.686
And I got her singing.

18:42.817 --> 18:44.471
Great voice.

18:44.601 --> 18:45.820
Just singing?

18:45.950 --> 18:47.822
Or is she a business too?

18:47.952 --> 18:49.215
What do you take me for,
Mr. Leyton?

18:49.345 --> 18:50.781
WOMAN:
I've got a name, you know.

18:58.049 --> 18:59.225
ZANEY: Mr. Leyton, Page Murdoch.

18:59.355 --> 19:01.923
Page. Nice name.

19:04.055 --> 19:06.536
Aren't you gonna offer
your star-turn a drink?

19:06.667 --> 19:07.972
Sorry.

19:08.103 --> 19:09.887
Vodka with ice and lemon.

19:10.018 --> 19:12.151
ZANEY: You should hear her.
PAGE: Don't forget the lemon.

19:12.281 --> 19:14.327
ZANEY: Shakespeare Sisters,
remember them?

19:14.457 --> 19:15.980
JACK: I know her
from somewhere,

19:16.111 --> 19:17.243
I'm sure we've met before.

19:17.373 --> 19:18.896
If you want me
to set you up...

19:19.027 --> 19:21.247
You're not pimping
her out, Zaney.

19:21.377 --> 19:23.118
Hey!

19:23.249 --> 19:24.685
You understand?

19:26.556 --> 19:27.992
Really?

19:28.123 --> 19:31.909
ZANEY: Yes! Two-nil.
Leyton's over the hill.

19:33.346 --> 19:37.437
♪

19:52.539 --> 19:53.931
PAGE SINGING:
♪ Up here on the moon

19:54.062 --> 19:55.803
Where do I know you from?

19:55.933 --> 19:57.413
What's that, Mr. Leyton?

19:57.544 --> 20:00.068
♪ Where the sky is low

20:02.505 --> 20:05.247
♪ Been wondering, lost

20:07.031 --> 20:10.818
♪ More unsure than strong

20:12.385 --> 20:15.301
♪ Between guilt and doubt

20:17.216 --> 20:19.740
♪ What is there to find

20:21.785 --> 20:23.309
♪ More than innocence

20:23.439 --> 20:24.440
I love you, Ronny.

20:24.571 --> 20:25.528
♪ Been drowning in dreams

20:25.659 --> 20:27.008
I know.

20:30.881 --> 20:33.232
You're nothing like Karim.

20:33.362 --> 20:36.104
♪ Drink

20:36.235 --> 20:40.021
♪ Drink to remember

20:40.151 --> 20:45.679
♪ When I drink and drink

20:45.809 --> 20:50.161
♪ Drink to dream

20:50.292 --> 20:52.599
♪ There's harm on the river

20:55.166 --> 20:58.648
♪ And the world stands still

21:00.171 --> 21:05.438
♪ You're my shadow

21:05.568 --> 21:09.442
♪ And you're my sins

21:09.572 --> 21:14.316
♪ I won't surrender

21:14.447 --> 21:19.234
♪ Till the new morning

21:19.365 --> 21:23.934
♪ Comes to take me back

21:24.065 --> 21:27.895
♪ Into the new light

21:28.025 --> 21:33.770
♪ When I drink, drink

21:33.901 --> 21:37.426
♪ Drink to remember

21:37.557 --> 21:43.171
♪ When I drink, drink

21:43.302 --> 21:44.346
♪ Drink to dream

21:44.477 --> 21:46.783
Page.

21:46.914 --> 21:48.568
Page Murdoch.

22:06.629 --> 22:09.197
VERONIQUE:
Drink to remember, Jack.

22:30.610 --> 22:32.351
[wings flapping]

23:04.861 --> 23:06.341
I know you like to watch me.

23:06.472 --> 23:08.387
I know you like
to watch me.

23:18.048 --> 23:19.746
What are you doing here?

23:24.141 --> 23:26.535
Not much of a guard dog,
is she?

23:27.841 --> 23:29.408
How did you know I lived here?

23:29.538 --> 23:31.192
Zaney told me.

23:32.889 --> 23:34.978
Why would he tell you that?

23:35.109 --> 23:36.589
I suppose he felt guilty

23:36.719 --> 23:40.767
after your little intervention
this afternoon.

23:40.897 --> 23:43.030
Very chivalrous, by the away.

23:45.336 --> 23:47.513
I wanted to say thanks.

23:48.949 --> 23:50.820
Personally.

23:50.951 --> 23:53.736
Are you gonna get me a drink?

23:59.002 --> 24:01.048
What are you having?

24:01.178 --> 24:03.311
Vodka with ice and lemon.

24:03.442 --> 24:04.834
Don't forget the lemon.

24:16.542 --> 24:18.544
Football fan, I see.

24:21.198 --> 24:22.548
How did you get over
to the island?

24:22.678 --> 24:23.549
Boat.

24:23.679 --> 24:25.855
I didn't see it.

24:31.295 --> 24:34.081
It's not safe to travel
across the water at night.

24:34.211 --> 24:36.083
What difference does it make?

24:36.213 --> 24:40.000
Night, day,
it's all the same here.

24:40.130 --> 24:42.393
I see you, you know?

24:42.524 --> 24:44.657
Shooting golf balls,

24:44.787 --> 24:47.964
boating up to that
lonely old church.

24:50.314 --> 24:52.099
What's over there?

24:52.229 --> 24:53.927
I've never seen you.

24:54.057 --> 24:56.712
It's a big lake.

25:02.065 --> 25:04.720
One thing
I've noticed about you.

25:06.940 --> 25:09.595
You drink every drink...

25:11.205 --> 25:14.077
as if it's going to be
your last.

25:15.862 --> 25:18.647
Zaney says
you're into real estate.

25:18.778 --> 25:21.694
Is that right?

25:21.824 --> 25:24.348
Says you're sitting
on a fortune.

25:24.479 --> 25:26.525
Some kind of tax dodge.

25:28.527 --> 25:30.833
What else does he say?

25:32.574 --> 25:35.011
How did you end up
in this hole?

25:35.142 --> 25:36.535
[chuckles]

25:36.665 --> 25:40.364
I like it. It's quiet.

25:40.495 --> 25:42.845
Don't you feel the world
is standing still here,

25:42.976 --> 25:45.892
waiting for someone
to tell you to move on?

25:47.023 --> 25:49.504
Where are you from, Page?

25:49.635 --> 25:51.245
Guess, Jack.

25:55.554 --> 25:58.774
[groans]

25:58.905 --> 26:01.908
Your wife, I like her hair.

26:02.038 --> 26:03.344
Where is she?

26:03.474 --> 26:04.650
She died.

26:09.568 --> 26:12.788
[groaning]

26:15.922 --> 26:19.926
Why didn't you go to Australia?

26:20.056 --> 26:22.581
Why didn't you
build Jack's Domain?

26:22.711 --> 26:25.279
Force her to go with you?
[echoing]

26:27.150 --> 26:29.283
'Cause you are not
strong enough.

26:29.413 --> 26:31.459
You lied about protecting her.

26:31.590 --> 26:33.069
You broke the contract,

26:33.200 --> 26:35.550
You let her die.
Remember, Jack?

26:40.990 --> 26:42.992
ANNOUNCER: Stracken scores!

26:44.907 --> 26:48.998
VERONIQUE: Penthouses,
luxury yachts, champagne.

26:51.610 --> 26:53.873
JACK: Let's look at the idea

26:54.003 --> 26:56.397
that my own team
are planning a new stadium.

26:58.225 --> 27:00.749
Ronny wanted
a piece of the action.

27:06.494 --> 27:08.365
JACK: I love you, Ronny.

27:08.496 --> 27:11.194
VERONIQUE: I know.

27:11.325 --> 27:13.022
JACK: Let's not do this.

27:13.153 --> 27:16.939
Where else can we
get the money then?

27:17.070 --> 27:18.985
There will be strings.

27:19.115 --> 27:21.378
There are always strings.

27:22.989 --> 27:24.294
Look.

27:26.732 --> 27:29.473
We get the 10 million,

27:29.604 --> 27:32.825
we build the new stadium,

27:32.955 --> 27:34.914
development deal.

27:40.223 --> 27:44.445
We pay him back,
and we never see his face again.

27:44.575 --> 27:45.925
Okay?

27:49.363 --> 27:50.712
Okay.

27:56.718 --> 27:59.155
Take us to Dover Street,
Mayfair, please, mate.

27:59.286 --> 28:00.635
VERONIQUE:
What are you doing?

28:00.766 --> 28:03.246
- Let's go to his place.
- Why?

28:03.377 --> 28:04.770
To ask him about the money.

28:04.900 --> 28:07.033
You want to do it?

28:07.163 --> 28:09.426
I don't see what other
choice we've got.

28:10.950 --> 28:14.388
Okay, but why now?

28:14.518 --> 28:16.782
We could see him anytime.

28:16.912 --> 28:18.784
If I'm gonna borrow money
from someone,

28:18.914 --> 28:21.787
I want to understand
who they are.

28:21.917 --> 28:23.092
He'll be there, right?

28:23.223 --> 28:25.225
Sure. It's his club.

28:29.011 --> 28:30.926
That's where you met him,
isn't it?

28:32.841 --> 28:34.713
You know it is.

28:34.843 --> 28:36.889
Why do you wanna see it?
There'll be--

28:37.019 --> 28:39.021
I know what kind of club
it is.

28:42.633 --> 28:45.593
In a place like that,
you'll have to participate.

28:45.724 --> 28:48.248
I'm cool with it.

28:48.378 --> 28:50.337
Are you?

28:50.467 --> 28:51.686
Yeah.

28:53.253 --> 28:57.126
♪ [electronic]

29:16.145 --> 29:19.496
JACK: Saul Karim,
night club entrepreneur,

29:19.627 --> 29:22.021
property tycoon,

29:22.151 --> 29:24.023
instigator of nightmares.

29:38.254 --> 29:39.821
Oh!

29:41.692 --> 29:44.043
What an honor this is.

29:44.173 --> 29:48.830
The great Jack Stracken
wants to borrow money from me

29:48.961 --> 29:51.920
to buy into his
old football club.

29:52.051 --> 29:55.358
You know, I'm a big fan
of you and your wife,

29:55.489 --> 29:59.101
about the good memory
of seeing her performing again,

29:59.232 --> 30:01.277
like your goal
in the Cup final.

30:01.408 --> 30:03.758
You always had the knack
for being in the right place

30:03.889 --> 30:05.368
at the right time.

30:05.499 --> 30:07.501
[chuckles]

30:07.631 --> 30:10.852
You're proposing
I lend against your stake

30:10.983 --> 30:13.507
in the new stadium.

30:13.637 --> 30:17.859
Share price rises,
you cash in and pay me back.

30:17.990 --> 30:21.558
I like it.
You are a shrewd man, Jack.

30:21.689 --> 30:22.821
[laughs]

30:22.951 --> 30:24.779
50% interest.

30:24.910 --> 30:26.041
JACK: No shit.

30:26.172 --> 30:28.696
It's my usual term.

30:28.827 --> 30:31.438
I'm sure a man
of your means and stature

30:31.568 --> 30:34.180
wouldn't expect anything less.

30:36.008 --> 30:39.446
These terms are not negotiable.

30:39.576 --> 30:41.361
JACK: We invested Karim's money in the football club

30:41.491 --> 30:43.537
as a new stadium was built.

30:43.667 --> 30:46.496
The share price soon went up.

30:48.803 --> 30:50.457
Do you like it?

30:50.587 --> 30:52.459
JACK: I'd never seen
Ronny so happy.

30:52.589 --> 30:53.677
We were killing it.

30:58.682 --> 31:00.510
JACK: I thought maybe
we should cash in,

31:00.641 --> 31:02.599
but Ronny always got her way.

31:02.730 --> 31:05.254
We agreed to build
this club together.

31:05.385 --> 31:07.561
You said you'd
go through with it,

31:07.691 --> 31:09.737
but now you're backing down.

31:09.868 --> 31:11.957
Please, a few more years.

31:12.087 --> 31:15.003
You always said Premier League
is the Holy Grail,

31:15.134 --> 31:18.920
then you can have as many
Jack's Domains as you want.

31:22.315 --> 31:24.447
[whining]

31:24.578 --> 31:25.796
No.

31:47.514 --> 31:48.602
[line rings]

31:48.732 --> 31:49.908
[phone ringing]

31:51.735 --> 31:52.911
Fleet.

31:53.041 --> 31:54.695
There was a girl here
last night.

31:54.825 --> 31:56.653
Oh, your luck's changing then.

31:56.784 --> 31:59.395
This is serious, Fleet.

31:59.526 --> 32:01.528
She know me how?

32:01.658 --> 32:04.618
What, do you need protection
from this girl?

32:04.748 --> 32:07.490
She's taken a picture.

32:07.621 --> 32:09.362
What picture?

32:09.492 --> 32:10.667
Oh, shit, the gun.

32:10.798 --> 32:11.712
What?

32:11.842 --> 32:14.236
The gun. Fuck!

32:14.367 --> 32:16.238
What the hell is
going on there, Jack?

32:17.892 --> 32:19.285
Calm down.

32:19.415 --> 32:20.939
You probably scared
the poor girl.

32:24.159 --> 32:26.074
I don't know
if Karim sent her.

32:26.205 --> 32:27.684
If Karim sent her,
you'd one dead fuck right now.

32:27.815 --> 32:29.382
- He just wants the money.
- Oh, come on, Jack.

32:29.512 --> 32:31.514
You're being paranoid.

32:31.645 --> 32:35.083
But I know
I've seen her before.

32:35.214 --> 32:37.607
Look, Fleet, I need
to ask you something.

32:37.738 --> 32:39.305
It's about Ronny's death.

32:44.571 --> 32:46.138
Was it my fault?

32:47.661 --> 32:49.880
You didn't kill her, did you?
He did.

32:50.011 --> 32:52.579
You get some rest.
You sound awful.

32:52.709 --> 32:55.582
All these overthinking,
it's not good for you.

33:02.545 --> 33:05.461
[coughing]

33:07.159 --> 33:08.638
JACK: Revenge?

33:08.769 --> 33:11.380
Possibly, but for what?

33:13.121 --> 33:16.124
Did Ronny have a sister?
Maybe it's her.

33:18.039 --> 33:19.693
Blackmail?

33:19.823 --> 33:22.696
She knows about the money,
wants a piece of it.

33:26.091 --> 33:28.397
Did Karim send her?

33:28.528 --> 33:31.052
The bastard
would come himself, surely.

33:37.667 --> 33:39.930
How does Page know about Ronny?

33:59.428 --> 34:03.084
[TV playing soccer game]

34:15.662 --> 34:17.707
Oi, watch it, fucker!

34:17.838 --> 34:19.492
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

34:19.622 --> 34:20.754
TV: He scores!

34:20.884 --> 34:22.060
I know you.

34:40.382 --> 34:43.342
JACK: It was happening,
my dream.

34:48.608 --> 34:50.697
But then it all went wrong.

34:57.443 --> 34:59.009
[speaking French]

35:00.185 --> 35:01.534
Whatever you want.

35:43.576 --> 35:46.405
I want you to want this club.

35:46.535 --> 35:48.058
I agreed, didn't I?

35:48.189 --> 35:49.408
Aus can wait.

35:52.019 --> 35:54.195
That is not the point.

35:55.979 --> 35:57.198
[sighs]

35:59.026 --> 36:01.898
Karim wants his money back.

36:05.032 --> 36:07.600
Back to fucking square one.

36:15.216 --> 36:17.175
What'd you want me to do?

36:23.485 --> 36:25.922
[party chatter]

36:30.057 --> 36:32.538
FLEET: Football agents
lining their pockets

36:32.668 --> 36:34.670
at the expense of the game.

36:34.801 --> 36:36.281
I blame the Prime League.

36:36.411 --> 36:38.239
A bit rich, coming from
a lawyer like you, Fleet.

36:38.370 --> 36:39.893
Oi!

36:40.023 --> 36:42.025
So now we've got
a little problem.

36:42.156 --> 36:43.462
We've got a problem?

36:43.592 --> 36:45.115
-I need to free up some capital.
-Oh, Jack.

36:45.246 --> 36:46.987
It's just a temporary thing.

36:47.117 --> 36:48.118
Well, how much are we talking?

36:48.249 --> 36:50.469
- Hey, Jack!
- Benny.

36:50.599 --> 36:53.036
Hi. You've come
a long way, Jack, eh?

36:53.167 --> 36:54.647
A far cry from Hackney Marshes,
don't you think?

36:54.777 --> 36:56.214
You too, Benny, you too.

36:56.344 --> 36:59.260
I know. I still remember
our trial back in the day.

36:59.391 --> 37:01.306
It was a lot, Benny.
I was just lucky that day.

37:01.436 --> 37:02.872
You've done all right
for yourself.

37:03.003 --> 37:05.048
Yeah, you know,
I'm just the money man, Jack.

37:05.179 --> 37:07.355
But you get the glory, eh?

37:07.486 --> 37:09.444
Yeah, look,
I'll see you later.

37:10.837 --> 37:12.099
Come back to me.

37:16.408 --> 37:17.409
FLEET: Jack!

37:19.280 --> 37:20.934
Councilor Lane.

37:21.064 --> 37:24.067
Ah, pleased to meet the one and
only Jack Stracken at last.

37:24.198 --> 37:25.765
I was just saying to Veronique

37:25.895 --> 37:28.376
what a fantastic development
you've made.

37:28.507 --> 37:30.465
Which is going to propel
Drayton United

37:30.596 --> 37:31.597
into the Prime League.

37:31.727 --> 37:32.989
I'll drink to that.

37:33.120 --> 37:36.079
Everyone, to the new stadium.

37:36.210 --> 37:37.646
ALL: New stadium!

37:37.777 --> 37:38.865
Cheers.

37:40.823 --> 37:42.129
Excuse me.

37:49.658 --> 37:50.703
Jack.

37:53.096 --> 37:55.490
You have gone quiet on me.

37:55.621 --> 37:57.492
I need more time.

38:00.016 --> 38:01.627
Ten days.

38:01.757 --> 38:04.064
And that's more than generous.

38:05.718 --> 38:07.589
Don't bite the hand, Jack.

38:18.731 --> 38:21.516
Uh, need a word.
Can't wait.

38:22.865 --> 38:24.911
Yeah.

38:25.041 --> 38:26.391
Stadium payments,
player contracts,

38:26.521 --> 38:27.696
developers, agents' fees.

38:27.827 --> 38:29.437
I've been through
all the figures.

38:29.568 --> 38:31.004
They just don't add up.

38:31.134 --> 38:32.919
What doesn't add up?

38:33.049 --> 38:34.399
Give us a minute, mate.

38:34.529 --> 38:35.617
Sure.

38:39.012 --> 38:40.796
Someone's stealing from us.

38:40.927 --> 38:43.321
And Karim wants his loan back.

38:43.451 --> 38:44.757
What did he say?

38:44.887 --> 38:47.281
What do you fucking think, Jack?

38:47.412 --> 38:49.109
[crowd chatter]

38:52.025 --> 38:54.462
- You--
- Shut up.

38:54.593 --> 38:55.985
Just do your job.

39:07.388 --> 39:08.346
Fuck.

39:11.827 --> 39:13.916
It's the transfer fees.

39:14.047 --> 39:15.440
How's that possible?

39:15.570 --> 39:18.399
20 million skimmed off
the transfer fees.

39:18.530 --> 39:21.054
Come on, Jack.
It's nothing at this level.

39:21.184 --> 39:23.143
He doesn't care about
the money.

39:23.273 --> 39:24.362
This is his game.

39:24.492 --> 39:27.147
- Karim?
- Yeah.

39:27.277 --> 39:29.454
Are you saying he'd bankrupt
the club intentionally?

39:29.584 --> 39:30.933
He'd lose his stake.
It doesn't make any sense.

39:31.064 --> 39:33.066
You don't know him
like I do.

39:33.196 --> 39:35.851
- I gonna fucking talk to him.
- Talk about what?

39:35.982 --> 39:37.418
We can't prove anything.

39:37.549 --> 39:38.985
He's too fucking smart.

39:39.115 --> 39:41.901
Someone is working for him.

39:42.031 --> 39:43.511
Someone here.

39:43.642 --> 39:45.034
Who?

39:45.165 --> 39:46.601
Benny?

39:46.732 --> 39:49.517
No. No fucking way.

39:49.648 --> 39:51.824
Benny's the one
who brought this to us.

39:51.954 --> 39:54.870
Okay, let's start with
the agents then.

39:56.481 --> 40:00.180
It's going to get nasty, Jack.

40:00.310 --> 40:02.835
Are you okay with that?

40:04.097 --> 40:05.751
JACK: Where's Page?

40:05.881 --> 40:07.883
ZANEY: Back home, I guess.

40:08.014 --> 40:09.189
And where's that?

40:09.319 --> 40:10.625
You're a sly one,
Mr. Leyton.

40:10.756 --> 40:13.759
I'm not pissing around, Zaney!

40:13.889 --> 40:15.891
Those holiday flats
they can't sell.

40:16.022 --> 40:17.850
One in the complex.

40:23.159 --> 40:25.074
FLEET: When was last time
Ronny was in the news?

40:25.205 --> 40:27.120
Years ago when she was died.

40:27.250 --> 40:30.558
Exactly. But I'll check it out
if it'll make you happy, Jack.

40:30.689 --> 40:33.300
What does she
call herself then?

40:33.431 --> 40:35.128
Her name's Page,
Page Murdoch.

40:35.258 --> 40:37.783
Find out who she is.
Do it now.

40:45.355 --> 40:47.314
JACK: Is it Page
triggering these memories?

40:47.445 --> 40:48.315
[thunderclap]

40:48.446 --> 40:49.577
On a bottle?

40:52.972 --> 40:55.409
Or am I losing
my fucking mind?

41:01.589 --> 41:02.634
VERONIQUE: Admit it.

41:02.764 --> 41:05.332
Then I'll forgive you.

41:13.514 --> 41:15.298
JACK: Admit what, Ronny?

41:15.429 --> 41:16.822
VERONIQUE: You know what.

41:28.398 --> 41:29.922
[thud]

41:30.052 --> 41:31.184
Stalking me now?

41:38.017 --> 41:39.888
Do you know what I do
to people like you?

41:40.019 --> 41:41.629
Pray tell.

41:41.760 --> 41:44.502
People who hit me in the head
with my own golf club.

41:44.632 --> 41:46.982
You fell over drunk
and bashed your head.

41:47.113 --> 41:48.027
Of course I did.

41:48.157 --> 41:49.811
You should be thanking me,

41:49.942 --> 41:53.119
getting you onto that sofa
in the shit state you were in.

41:53.249 --> 41:54.990
What are you doing?
Hey, stop!

41:55.121 --> 41:57.123
- What do you want from me?
- [distant chatter]

41:57.253 --> 41:58.951
Hey, Thomas!

42:00.039 --> 42:01.083
Catch.

42:03.564 --> 42:05.000
Hey!

42:05.131 --> 42:07.176
Why didn't you build
Jack's Domain,

42:07.307 --> 42:09.614
force her to go with you?

42:12.181 --> 42:15.141
I need a word.
It can't wait.

42:16.708 --> 42:19.145
JACK: Need a word.
Can't wait.

42:21.495 --> 42:25.020
[Radio playing soccer game]

42:25.151 --> 42:28.850
ANNOUNCER: Crosses Goode,
Murdoch sweeps. Stracken!

42:28.981 --> 42:30.548
Jack Stracken scores!

42:33.986 --> 42:35.901
Come back to me, Jack.

42:37.816 --> 42:38.947
Page?

42:42.429 --> 42:44.257
VERONIQUE:
I just want you to remember!

42:44.387 --> 42:45.824
Page.

42:50.089 --> 42:51.133
Hey!

42:54.528 --> 42:57.270
[panting]

43:05.321 --> 43:07.628
Don't let them hurt me.

43:07.759 --> 43:08.847
[gunshot]

43:12.241 --> 43:14.983
Hey, where is she?

43:15.114 --> 43:16.985
Mr. Leyton,
last time you came here--

43:17.116 --> 43:19.379
I'm sorry, okay?

43:19.509 --> 43:21.729
[scooter approaching]

43:21.860 --> 43:23.818
There's your Page.

43:25.472 --> 43:27.343
Come back to me, Jack.

43:27.474 --> 43:30.042
[scooter engine]

43:43.795 --> 43:45.318
[motor stops]

43:50.584 --> 43:52.107
[motor starts]

44:13.825 --> 44:14.913
Page.

44:47.380 --> 44:49.077
[phone ringing]

44:52.994 --> 44:53.908
Yo.

44:54.039 --> 44:55.301
JACK: Grant?

44:55.431 --> 44:56.737
GRANT: Pegged you
for a dead man.

44:56.868 --> 44:58.043
I'm a dead man
calling in a favor.

44:58.173 --> 44:59.697
It's been a long time, mate.

44:59.827 --> 45:01.307
I wouldn't be calling
if it wasn't important.

45:01.437 --> 45:02.482
I'm retired, so...

45:02.612 --> 45:04.092
You owe me.
You know you do.

45:04.223 --> 45:06.007
I don't know what you're
talking about, mate.

45:06.138 --> 45:08.706
Look, Jack,
I know you love her.

45:08.836 --> 45:11.230
I don't wanna fucking hear
about it, Grant, all right?

45:11.360 --> 45:13.841
I need you to sniff around
Drayton FC,

45:13.972 --> 45:15.843
see if there's any record
of a Page Murdoch.

45:15.974 --> 45:18.541
- Who?
- French girl, auburn hair.

45:18.672 --> 45:19.760
French girl.

45:19.891 --> 45:22.328
I know. She's got eyes on us.

45:22.458 --> 45:24.330
Check it out. Go right back
to before I went away.

45:24.460 --> 45:26.201
Look, mate,
I never wanna go back there.

45:26.332 --> 45:27.855
The more I see this girl,
the more I see Ronny.

45:27.986 --> 45:29.944
And the more I see Ronny,
the more I remember.

45:30.075 --> 45:31.337
You were there that night.

45:31.467 --> 45:32.555
This could be bad
for both of us.

45:32.686 --> 45:34.035
This girl knows something.

45:34.166 --> 45:35.776
She stole a picture.

45:35.907 --> 45:37.865
I just wanna know
who this girl is.

45:37.996 --> 45:39.562
Maybe some connection
with Karim.

45:39.693 --> 45:41.477
What's this picture?

45:41.608 --> 45:44.176
It was Ronny in a red dress.

45:44.306 --> 45:45.568
You know the one.

45:45.699 --> 45:47.440
Well, look, mate, what--

45:47.570 --> 45:50.486
Why don't you just talk
to Fleet, straight up?

45:50.617 --> 45:52.314
Because you are the only one
I can trust.

45:52.445 --> 45:54.447
Something not right here.

45:56.928 --> 45:57.798
Grant?

45:59.800 --> 46:00.758
Grant?

46:03.456 --> 46:06.938
Just a couple of questions,
then we're even, yeah?

46:07.068 --> 46:08.243
Then we're even.

46:08.374 --> 46:10.332
Well, um...

46:10.463 --> 46:12.465
I won't get much out of Fleet.

46:12.595 --> 46:14.684
She's a cagey character.

46:14.815 --> 46:18.514
I could try the councilor.

46:18.645 --> 46:19.646
Lane?

46:20.952 --> 46:22.518
JACK: Well, it won't be easy.

46:22.649 --> 46:23.868
Lane's dead.

46:31.527 --> 46:35.140
FLEET: Mr. Grant,
it's been awhile.

46:35.270 --> 46:38.796
So you've been running things
in Mr. Stracken's absence.

46:38.926 --> 46:40.275
We have an agreement.

46:40.406 --> 46:42.800
Until he deems it safe
to come home.

46:42.930 --> 46:44.627
I just wish we knew
where he was.

46:44.758 --> 46:47.587
We'd be far more helpful to him.

46:47.717 --> 46:50.155
How does he seem to you?

46:50.285 --> 46:52.853
He's been a bit...

46:52.984 --> 46:54.899
erratic on the phone.

46:55.029 --> 46:58.163
I know about
as much as you do.

47:02.123 --> 47:03.777
Mm. In your phone call,

47:03.908 --> 47:05.735
you mentioned something
about a girl?

47:05.866 --> 47:07.085
Yes.

47:11.829 --> 47:13.265
Page Murdoch.

47:13.395 --> 47:15.484
Yeah, I forgot you used
to be on the force.

47:15.615 --> 47:17.791
The name doesn't
ring any bells.

47:23.318 --> 47:27.279
You've certainly hit
the big time, haven't you?

47:27.409 --> 47:30.586
Like I say,
just keeping his seat for him.

47:30.717 --> 47:32.414
And of course,
promotion to the Prime League

47:32.545 --> 47:34.025
certainly helped.

47:34.155 --> 47:37.028
I'd also like to talk
to other old associates

47:37.158 --> 47:38.594
of Mr. Stracken's.

47:38.725 --> 47:40.901
You know, people like...

47:41.032 --> 47:43.991
Saul Karim, for instance.

47:47.603 --> 47:50.432
Come on, Fleet.

47:50.563 --> 47:53.609
Well, then you'll know
that Karim disappeared.

47:53.740 --> 47:56.874
I've no idea where he is,
as Jack will testify.

47:57.004 --> 47:59.050
I'm sorry I can't be
of any more help,

47:59.180 --> 48:02.792
but if that's all,
I do have rather a lot on.

48:04.272 --> 48:05.404
Yes.

48:08.929 --> 48:12.715
Thank you for clarifying things.

48:12.846 --> 48:15.762
Do give my regards to Jack,
won't you?

48:30.690 --> 48:32.213
There you are, Fleet.

48:32.344 --> 48:33.258
[tires screeching]

48:42.223 --> 48:44.399
PAGE: You drink every drink...

48:46.184 --> 48:48.708
as if it's going
to be your last.

48:50.666 --> 48:51.667
Page.

48:52.842 --> 48:54.714
♪ [disco]

48:56.759 --> 48:58.674
JACK: They were lovers.

49:08.510 --> 49:09.555
[engine stops]

49:14.255 --> 49:15.126
[beep]

49:27.616 --> 49:31.272
You know what I'm saying?
Totally off-speed. Every time.

49:31.403 --> 49:33.622
